# Avoid Premature Optimization

Prefer clear, maintainable code over micro-optimizations until there is evidence of a real performance problem.

## Guidelines

- Use `useMemo`, `useCallback`, or `React.memo` only when really needed
- Don't add them "just in case" or for cheap computations (small arrays, simple object creation, basic arithmetic)
- Add them only when:
  - You have measured a performance issue (profiler, benchmarks)
  - The computation is demonstrably expensive (large data, heavy transforms)
  - The optimization clearly addresses that issue
  - The benefit outweighs the added complexity
- Simpler code is easier to reason about and maintain
- Premature optimizations add complexity and can introduce bugs
